  <brief_title>Adverse Event Scale in Patients With Epilepsy (aEscape) - A European Survey for Physicians With Epilepsy Patients</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Multicenter, Non-interventional Surveillance Study to Evaluate the Adverse Effects of Antiepileptic Drug Treatment in Patients With Epilepsy</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>UCB Pharma</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
    <collaborator>
      <agency>International Bureau for Epilepsy</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </collaborator>
  </sponsors>
  <source>UCB Pharma</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the survey is to explore through a structured interview and patient
      examination the rate and distribution of neurological and systemic adverse effects related to
      antiepileptic treatment. Adverse effects and considerations to modify the therapy will be
      assessed in pediatric and adult patients with controlled as well as uncontrolled epilepsy
      with different seizure types
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
